# } Listing 21-16: Modifying ThreadPool to store the sender of a channel that transmits Job instances In ThreadPool::new, we create our new channel and have the pool hold the sender. This will successfully compile. Let’s try passing a receiver of the channel into each worker as the thread pool creates the channel. We know we want to use the receiver in the thread that the workers spawn, so we’ll reference the receiver parameter in the closure. The code in Listing 21-17 won’t quite compile yet. Filename: src/lib.rs # use std::{sync::mpsc, thread};
